parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion/rusting of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to operate, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rust holes in the frame
corrosion on the subframe
punctures in the main subframe
frame collapse
motor mount sinking into the frame
and rust near the catalytic converters.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to disclose frame corrosion/rusting can lead to owners unknowingly operating an unsafe vehicle, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Lack of notification about frame corrosion/rusting
failure to disclose during recall repairs
and failure to inspect the frame during routine maintenance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Holes and cracks in the frame
rust and corrosion on the frame
detachment of the fuel tank
and instability in the handling of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the leaf springs can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fractured or broken leaf springs
loud noises coming from the rear of the vehicle
and detachment of the brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate response to recalls and repairs can lead to further damage to the vehicle and put the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Delayed or unavailable repairs
refusal to honor recalls
and lack of communication from the manufacturer and dealerships.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
often when the driver is braking or shifting gears. The accelerator pedal may stick or jam
causing the engine to rev excessively. In some cases
the vehicle may lurch forward or accelerate rapidly
making it difficult for the driver to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Floor mat interference can cause unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The floor mat may interfere with the accelerator pedal
causing it to stick or jam. This can lead to unintended acceleration
especially when the driver is braking or shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sticking or racing throttle can cause unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The throttle may stick or race
causing the engine to rev excessively. This can lead to unintended acceleration
especially when the driver is braking or shifting gears.
